<strong>Gov. Abdullahi Ganduje By Zubairu Idris Gov. Abdullahi Ganduje of Kano state has approved the appointment of Baffa Babba Dan-Agundi as Acting Managing Director of Kano state Consumer Protection Council (KSCPC). This is contained in a statement issued by the Chief Press Secretary to the governor, Mr Abba Anwar, on Monday in Kano. Anwar said that the appointment was with immediate effect, pending the appointment of a substantive Managing Director. “As Acting MD, he will look into all corners of the commission, both operational and others, with the view to putting things in good shape, before a substantive Managing Director is appointed,” he said. The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports that Dan-Agundi is the Managing Director of the Kano Road Transport Agency (KAROTA). NAN reports that the KSCPC Mangeing Director, Gen. Idris Bello Dambazau (rtd) resigned his appointment voluntarily.(NAN) (www.nannews.ng) Edited by Dorcas Jonah/Julius Toba-Jegede